        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The recipient is identified by the cover that accompanies the letter. Gordon was the minister of Birnie, near Elgin, Scotland. He was an expert on the flora of Morayshire.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Gordon had contributed catalogues of plants from certain parts of Scotland to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4975.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Hewett Cottrell Watson’s</ref> <hi rend="italic">New botanists’ guide</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_8198.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Watson 1835–7</ref>).</note>
